Alison Hargreaves, 32, was swept to her death in 260mph winds on her way down from the Himalayan mountain in 1995 .
Her son Tom Ballard, 26, plans to climb the summit of K2, 20 years after his mother died .
Mr Ballard, who is one of the world's most accomplished climbers, said he saw it as his destiny to follow in her footsteps .